To allow us to upload your new site or make revisions to an old one, we will need to be able to access your site from the backend to streamline the process.

We prefer the WordPress platform for building sites. If you're already in the fold we'll need administrative access to your account. If not, we can help.

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3" _builder_version="3.0.47" parallax="off" parallax_method="on" use_background_color_gradient="off" background_color_gradient_start="#3D72E7" background_color_gradient_end="#53a0fe" background_color_gradient_direction="243deg"][et_pb_blurb title="Your Contact Info" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%153%%" icon_color="#535B7C" use_icon_font_size="on" icon_font_size="49px" _builder_version="3.17.6" header_font="Nunito Sans|700|||||||" header_text_color="#000000" header_line_height="1.4em" body_font="Nunito Sans|600|||||||" body_text_color="#000000" body_font_size="16px" background_color="#ffffff" border_radii="on|4px|4px|4px|4px" border_color_all="#E02B20" border_width_top="6px" border_color_top="#0C71C3" border_color_bottom="#126e3d" box_shadow_style="preset3" box_shadow_color="rgba(34,56,101,0.12)" text_orientation="center" custom_margin="|||" custom_padding="54px|20px|60px|20px" filter_opacity="81%" animation_style="zoom" animation_intensity_zoom="5%"]

Your best email along with a link to your preferred video chat software (we love Zoom) and a phone number if you like a bit of the Old School approach. 

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3" _builder_version="3.0.47" parallax="off" parallax_method="on" use_background_color_gradient="off" background_color_gradient_start="#3D72E7" background_color_gradient_end="#53A0FE" background_color_gradient_direction="243deg"][et_pb_blurb title="Your Down Payment" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%155%%" icon_color="#535B7C" use_icon_font_size="on" icon_font_size="49px" _builder_version="3.17.6" header_font="Nunito Sans|700|||||||" header_text_color="#000000" header_line_height="1.4em" body_font="Nunito Sans|600|||||||" body_text_color="#000000" body_font_size="16px" background_color="#ffffff" border_radii="on|4px|4px|4px|4px" border_color_all="#E02B20" border_width_top="6px" border_color_top="#0C71C3" border_color_bottom="#126e3d" box_shadow_style="preset3" box_shadow_color="rgba(34,56,101,0.12)" text_orientation="center" custom_margin="|||" custom_padding="54px|20px|60px|20px" filter_opacity="81%" animation_style="zoom" animation_intensity_zoom="5%"]

Yes, as a sign of good faith and a way to keep the lights on, we ask for a 50% payment of initial cost projections before beginning a project.

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" admin_label="Features CTA Section" _builder_version="3.17.6" background_color="#000000" custom_padding="0|0px|14px|0px|false|false" saved_tabs="all"][et_pb_row custom_padding="43px|0px|27px|0px|false|false" _builder_version="3.17.6"][et_pb_column type="4_4" _builder_version="3.17.6" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.17.6" text_font="||||||||" text_font_size="62px" text_font_size_phone="44px" text_font_size_last_edited="on|phone"]

What's next?

[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" admin_label="Clients Logos" _builder_version="3.0.83" background_color="#f8fbfe" custom_padding="0|0px|0|0px|false|false"][et_pb_row custom_padding="27px|0px|7px|0px|false|false" _builder_version="3.17.6"][et_pb_column type="4_4" _builder_version="3.17.6" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.17.6" text_font="|600|||||||" text_font_size="17px"]

Once the above six points have been met we will begin working through the 4 phases of the creation process listed below.

[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row custom_padding="30px|0px|0|0px|false|false" _builder_version="3.17.6"][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="3.17.6" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_toggle title="Phase 1: Discover" open_toggle_background_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_text_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_background_color="#353535" icon_color="#ffffff" _builder_version="3.17.6" title_level="h2" title_font="|600|||||||" title_text_align="center" title_text_color="#000000" border_width_all="0px" border_color_all="#353535"]

In this phase we will discuss and evaluate the current state of your web presence and look for ways to leverage and improve it via the modification of your current site or, if need be, the creation of an entirely new one. We will focus on a dialogue in which your needs, goals and direction as a business are put into proper context. We will "discover", as the name of the phase implies, both 1) what exactly we can do to help you and 2) what you have in mind in that regard.

From there we will offer an initial assessment that will include:

 

  • areas to be improved upon such as the general user experience and design features to enhance the impression given to your visiting clientel
  • suggested services including what we intend to build for you and recommendations to help leverage your web presence
  • a preliminary website design in the form of a "wireframe" or "mockup" (graphic document) to be used as a working model as we move forward through the remaining three phases

After the initial assessment has been approved we will form a contractual agreement outlining the specific features, functionality and layout of your website.

[/et_pb_toggle][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="3.17.6" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_toggle title="Phase 2: Design" open_toggle_background_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_text_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_background_color="#353535" icon_color="#ffffff" _builder_version="3.17.6" title_level="h2" title_font="|600|||||||" title_text_align="center" title_text_color="#000000" border_width_all="0px" border_color_all="#353535"]

This phase is where the real creative work begins. Here we will take the information gained in phase 1 and put it into form. The preliminary design generated in phase 1 will be built into an actual functioning website. We will essentially be taking the results of the Discovery phase and putting them into digital form to give you an initial taste of what is to come through our collaboration. This is where you will be able to "test drive" your new website.

By the end of phase 2 you should expect:

 

  • a working prototype of your website with full online functionality including the implementation of any inbound contact channels and other media
  • the chance to test it to gain insights into any changes you would like to see implemented
  • a better understanding of where your project is going and the form your new web presence is taking

Once feedback on the initial website prototype has been gathered, we will move forward with refining and finetuning it into a launch ready production model via Phase 3.

[/et_pb_toggle][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row custom_padding="20px|0px|30px|0px|false|false" _builder_version="3.17.6"][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="3.17.6" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_toggle title="Phase 3: Refine" open_toggle_background_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_text_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_background_color="#353535" icon_color="#ffffff" _builder_version="3.17.6" title_level="h2" title_font="|600|||||||" title_text_align="center" title_text_color="#000000" border_width_all="0px" border_color_all="#353535"]

Phase 3 offers the chance for all insights gained via the initial design process to be implemented. Where Phase 2, the design process, can be considered a "rough draft" of your new website Phase 3 is preparation for commercial publication. 

This is the point where we will work with you to put the finishing touches on your new and improved web presence in order to prepare it for deployment into the market. The key word here is "refine" meaning we will work together to tune in on the finer points of how best to streamline the platform and wow your clientele.

Key points addressed in Phase 3 will include:

 

  • ascertainment of key revisions desired
  • implementations of these revisions
  • confirmation of mutual fulfillment of the project's contract

By the end of Phase 3 your website will be finished. The only remaining thing to be done will be the fulfillment of any remaining contractual obligations including but not limited to payment of the remaing cost and the hand off of the website to the client.

[/et_pb_toggle][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="3.17.6" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_toggle title="Phase 4: Launch" open_toggle_background_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_text_color="#ffffff" closed_toggle_background_color="#353535" icon_color="#ffffff" _builder_version="3.17.6" title_level="h2" title_font="|600|||||||" title_text_align="center" title_text_color="#000000" border_width_all="0px" border_color_all="#353535"]

Phase 4 is where we "hand you the keys", so to speak, to your new site and "our work here is done". We do, of course offer maintanence services and the opportunity for future business together should you be interested.

The launch phase is the moment where the new website becomes YOUR site and where you can begin to make the most of your new and improved web presence to leverage your business and the impact you have on your audience.

By the end of the launch phase clients should expect:

 

  • a fully functioning and optimized website with all content submitted and design revisions implemented
  • an excellent relationship with us here at Signal Works Design
  • a chance to make the most of their new web presence in the market

Phase 4 means the happy completion of the project but we will always be here in the future should you have any questions or need to call on us for our services in the future.
